Grade Tracking System

A console-based Java application for managing students, courses, enrollments, grades, reports, and persistent data storage**.

This system allows schools, teachers, and students to track academic performance efficiently with features such as grade calculation, reporting, database viewing, and CSV export

Features Overview

8. View Database
9. Search Database
10. Save Data
11. Load Data
12. Export Student Report
13. Exit Program

Feature Explanations

View Database
Menu Option: 8
Location: `Main.java → viewDatabase()`

The Virew Database menu provides an overview of all stored students and courses.

Sub-Options

1. View All Courses - Lists all courses with credits and number of enrolled students. Includes optional detailed view with grading weights and enrolled student names.

2. View All Students - Shows every student with SR Code, name, major, and number of enrolled courses. Optional detailed summaries include grades per course. 

3. Database Overview - Displays statistics: total students, total courses, total enrollments, average courses per student, and top 3 most popular courses. 

4. Back - Returns to the main menu.                                                                                                                         
Purpose
Provides a fast, readable way to inspect database contents.
Great for administrators performing audits or quick checks.

Search Database
Menu Option: 9
Location: `GradeTracker.java → searchDatabase()`

Allows keyword-based searching across courses and students.

Search Options

| Option        | Searches                         |
| --------------| -------------------------------- |
| 1. Courses    | Matches course code or name.     |
| 2. Students   | Matches SR-Code, name, or major. |

How It Works?

- Converts input to lowercase
- Checks database fields for partial matches
- Displays all matching records

Purpose
Makes it easy to find specific data in large datasets—ideal for registrars and instructors.

Save Data
Menu Option: 10
Location: `GradeTracker.java → saveAllData()`

Saves all system data so progress is never lost.

Files Saved to `/data`

| File              | Contains                        |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------- |
|  students.dat     | Serialized student objects      |
|  courses.dat      | Serialized course objects       |
|  enrollments.csv  | Enrollments (Student ↔ Course)  |
|  grades.csv       | All student grades              |
| courses.csv       | Course details + weight schemes |

Purpose
Ensures all academic information persists after closing the program.

Load Data
Menu Option: 11
Location: `GradeTracker.java → loadAllData()`

Loads previously saved files from the `/data` folder.
What Gets Restored
- List of students
- Courses
- Enrollments
- Grades
- Assignment names
- Grading weights

Purpose
Restores the exact state of the system from the last save—ideal for long-term or repeated usage.

Export Report
Menu Option: 12
Location: `GradeTracker.java → exportStudentReport()`

Exports a detailed student performance report to a text file.
Report Includes
- Student info (Name, SR-Code, Major)
- All enrolled courses
- Final numerical & letter grades
- Assignment category breakdowns and averages

Example Output

STUDENT REPORT
==============
Name: John Doe
SR Code: SR-001
Major: BSIT

       COURSES AND GRADES:
=================================
CS101 - Programming 1: 92.50% (A)
  Homework: 88.00% (4 assignments)
  Exams: 95.00% (2 assignments)

Purpose
Creates printable, shareable academic reports.

Exit
Menu Option: 13
Location: `Main.java → case 13`

What Happens When Exiting
- System automatically saves all data
- Displays “Goodbye!”
- Program closes safely

Purpose
Protects the user from accidental data loss.

